President Nana Akufo-Addo of Ghana yesterday spoke with President Muhammadu Buhari, expressing his sincere apology over the demolition of a building on the premises of Nigerian High Commission in Accra, Ghana. This was contained in a statement issued by Presidential spokesman, Garba Shehu. According to him, in a telephone call, the Ghanaian leader told President Buhari that he has directed full investigation into the incident. Earlier in the day, it was revealed that some suspects had been arrested and would be arraigned in court. 